page.title: 14HINCKLEY - TYPICAL STREET
page.content: Seaforth Drive is a big road with lots of houses. We counted 30 houses on the left hand side and 34 on the right. It took us 5 mins and 30 seconds going down Seaforth Drive and 5 mins and 45 seconds going up. Seaforth Drive is on a hill. Most of the houses were made of bricks and tiles. On Seaforth Drive number 99 was called Timbucktoo. On the corner of Seaforth Drive is number 101. We asked the owner how old the house was and it was 12 years old. We saw 20 cars and 11 vans. We also saw 6 lamposts and 14 signs. There were 54 semi-detached houses. Nearly all the houses had wood cladding between the windows. Seaforth Drive is a typical Hinckley estate road.
